DataElement.preferredDefinition: A microarray is a piece of glass or plastic on which different samples have been affixed at separate locations in an ordered manner thus forming a microscopic array.  The samples are usually DNA fragments but may also be antibodies, other proteins, or tissues.:A collection or single item of factual information, derived from measurement or research, from which conclusions may be drawn._A Uniform Resource Locator is an Internet address which tells a browser where to find an Internet resource. (from http://www.computeruser.com)_Generic value domain for a java datatype that is a class that represents character strings.
